quran[8]{c,v,t,f}:
  33,55,"No sin is committed by them{1}regarding their fathers or their sons or their brothers or their brothers’ sons or their sisters’ sons or their women or those whom they rightfully possess. Yet be mindful{2}of Allah; indeed, Allah has always been a Witness over everything.",footnotes:1:The wives of the Prophet (peace be upon him).|2:The form of the verb used indicates that Allah is addressing the wives of the Prophet (peace be upon him).
  33,56,"Indeed, Allah and His angels give blessings{1}to the Prophet. O you who have attained faith, pray for blessings upon him and greet him with a prayer of peace.",footnotes:1:Literally ‘prayers’.
  33,57,"Indeed, those who hurt Allah and His Messenger— Allah has cursed them in the Earlier<i class=""s"">(Life) </i>and the Hereafter, and has prepared for them a demeaning punishment."
  33,58,"And those who hurt believing men and believing women for acts they did not earn have surely burdened themselves with perjury and evident sin."
  33,59,"O Prophet, tell your spouses and your daughters and the women of the believers to make their outer garments hang low over them; that is more likely that they will be recognized and not hurt. And Allah has always been Oft-Forgiving, Bestowing of mercy."
  33,60,"If the hypocrites do not desist, as well as those with sickness in their hearts and the rumormongers in the City<i class=""s"">(of Madinah) </i>, We will surely incite you<a class=""sup""><sup>sg </sup></a>against them; then they will not neighbor you in it except for a short while."
  33,61,"Accursed; wherever they are found, they should be captured and relentlessly killed outright."
  33,62,"Such has been Allah’s rule with those who passed on before, and you<a class=""sup""><sup>sg </sup></a>will never find any change in Allah’s rule."
